page("settings", "Settings",
     "Cachly settings: coordinate format, units, map options and sources, custom map URLs, themes and dark mode, navigation app, logging, proximity sounds and tracking.",
     "Settings", "Settings",
     "Settings (in the <strong>More</strong> tab) is where you tailor Cachly to how you cache. The screen is <strong>searchable</strong> &mdash; type in the search box at the top to jump to an option by name &mdash; and is organized into the categories below.",
"""        <h2 id="categories">Settings categories</h2>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>What you configure</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>Cachly Pro</strong></td><td>Your <a href="cachly-pro.html">Pro</a> subscription and premium features.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Users</strong></td><td>Your account(s), including the additional accounts used for <a href="logging.html#multi-user">multi-user logging</a>.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>General</strong></td><td>App-wide preferences, including <strong>coordinate format</strong> (DDM/DMS/decimal &mdash; see <a href="waypoints.html#formats">formats</a>) and <strong>units</strong> (distance/elevation).</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Map Options &amp; Navigation</strong></td><td>Map source &amp; style, overlays, custom map URL, <a href="map.html#sync-position">Sync Live &amp; Offline Map Position</a>, and which external app handles driving directions. <a href="#map-options">Details &darr;</a></td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Tracking and Routes</strong> <span class="pro-badge">PRO</span></td><td>Options for <a href="map.html#route-tracking">recording and importing</a> your caching tracks.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Caches &amp; Waypoints</strong></td><td>How caches and <a href="waypoints.html">waypoints</a> are displayed and handled.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Logs</strong></td><td>Logging behavior and log-type options.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Templates</strong></td><td>Reusable <a href="logging.html#templates">text templates</a> for your logs.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Cachly Intelligence</strong> <span class="pro-badge">PRO</span></td><td>Turn on AI log help, pick a <a href="intelligence.html">provider/model</a>, edit writing prompts and enter API keys.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Proximity Alert</strong></td><td>Audio alert as you near a cache. <a href="#proximity">Details &darr;</a></td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Trackables</strong></td><td><a href="trackables.html">Trackable</a> options, including auto-visit.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Highlighting</strong></td><td><a href="search.html#highlights">Highlight</a> colors and rules.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Imports &amp; Pocket Queries</strong></td><td><a href="import-export.html">GPX import and pocket query</a> handling.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Dark Mode</strong></td><td>Follow the system appearance or force light/dark.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Below the categories you&rsquo;ll also find <strong>Manage Subscriptions</strong> and <strong>Restore Purchases</strong> (see <a href="cachly-pro.html#restore">Cachly Pro</a>).</p>

        <h2 id="map-options">Map Options &amp; Navigation</h2>
        <p>Choose your <strong>map source</strong> and style, configure overlays and POI layers, and add a <strong>custom map URL</strong> for your own tile server. These settings drive what you see on <a href="map.html">The Map</a>.</p>
        <p><strong>API keys.</strong> Some map sources need a free key entered here: <strong>Thunderforest</strong> for Open Cycle maps, and a <strong>Bing Maps</strong> key for online UK Ordnance Survey maps (added via Add Custom Tile URL &rarr; UK OS preset).</p>
        <p><strong>Navigation apps (routing providers).</strong> The &#8943; menu on the <a href="map.html#compass">Navigate to Cache</a> screen can hand off to any installed app: Apple Maps, Google Maps, Waze, Navigon, Topo Maps, HERE Maps, TomTom / TomTom Go, GPS Navigation&nbsp;-&nbsp;Scout, Guru, Maps.me, Gaia GPS, Pocket Earth, Sygic and Magic Earth. An app only appears if it&rsquo;s installed; set your default under Navigation.</p>

        <h2 id="proximity">Proximity Alert</h2>
        <p>Cachly can play an <strong>audio alert</strong> when you get close to a cache, so you can keep your phone pocketed on the approach. Configure the sound and trigger distance here.</p>
""")

page("apple-watch", "Apple Watch",
     "Cachly on Apple Watch: nearby caches, compass navigation, quick logging, waypoints, lists, photos and attributes on your wrist.",
     "Apple Watch", "Cachly on Apple Watch",
     "Cachly&rsquo;s Apple Watch app puts the essentials on your wrist &mdash; find nearby caches, follow the compass to one, and log it &mdash; without reaching for your phone.",
"""        <h2 id="overview">What the Watch app does</h2>
        <p>The Watch app syncs with your iPhone (via WatchConnectivity) and focuses on the in-the-field essentials:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Nearby caches</strong> &mdash; a list of caches around you.</li>
          <li><strong>Compass navigation</strong> &mdash; direction and distance to the selected cache.</li>
          <li><strong>Cache details</strong> &mdash; the key info, attributes and photos.</li>
          <li><strong>Waypoints</strong> &mdash; the cache&rsquo;s waypoints.</li>
          <li><strong>Quick logging</strong> &mdash; record a find or DNF from your wrist.</li>
          <li><strong>Lists &amp; search options</strong> &mdash; browse lists and set simple search filters (type, size).</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout tip">
          <span class="callout-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#8986;</span>
          <div class="callout-body">For caches in an <a href="lists.html#offline">offline set</a>, the Watch can show details without needing the iPhone to be online.</div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="home-screen">Home screen &amp; complications</h2>
        <p>The Watch app works as a <strong>complication</strong> on most watch faces for one-tap launching. Its home screen offers four ways in:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Nearby</strong> &mdash; loads geocaches within a nearby radius.</li>
          <li><strong>Current</strong> &mdash; the cache you&rsquo;re currently (or were last) viewing on your iPhone.</li>
          <li><strong>Lists</strong> &mdash; your offline and online cache lists.</li>
          <li><strong>Saved</strong> &mdash; caches stored directly on the watch.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="compass">Why the compass needs you to move (older watches)</h2>
        <p>On <strong>Apple Watch Series 5 and later</strong>, Cachly shows a true compass that updates as you turn, even standing still. <strong>Earlier models have no compass sensor</strong>, so Cachly derives heading from GPS course &mdash; which only works while you&rsquo;re moving. If your compass won&rsquo;t update while stationary, that&rsquo;s the hardware; a Series 5 or newer resolves it.</p>

        <h2 id="logging-on-watch">Logging from the Watch</h2>
        <p>Found it on a quick walk? Log it directly on the Watch. The log syncs back through your iPhone and follows the same <a href="logs.html#pending">pending/upload</a> flow as logs written on the phone.</p>
""")

